snippet: Parliament is expected to dissolve itself on Monday, with the popular vote scheduled for Sept. 4, rather than October 2013.
abstract: Israeli Prime Min Benjamin Netanyahu calls for early elections, one year ahead of schedule, saying it is more important to establish political stability than allow for full election cycle.
lead_paragraph: Parliament is expected to dissolve itself on Monday, with the popular vote scheduled for Sept. 4, rather than October 2013.

headline.seo: Netanyahu Calls for Early Israeli Elections
headline.main: Netanyahu Calls for Early Elections in Israel
headline.print_headline: Citing ‘Political Instability,’ and Vowing Victory, Netanyahu Calls for Early Elections
